    "comment": "Rationale: The paper uses the RiboTag-mouse (epitope tagged mouse RPL22) to visualize axonal translation in the visual system. Fig. 1 shows the localization of RPL22 (via HA-tag) in axon terminals of the superior colliculus (in retina).\n\n13/10/2017 Pim\n- Localization to ribosomes is not shown directly but inferred from well established role of RPL22 as ribosomal protein and author intent.. Experimental description: In order to isolate mRNAs translated in RGC axon terminals in the SC in vivo, we used the RiboTag knock-in mouse line (p. 182).\n\n13/10/2017 Pim\n- The ribotag mouse expresses a HA-tagged version of the exisiting mouse RPL22 gene.",
